  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper reports a sulfur-vacancy-rich ZnIn2S4/MoSe2 heterostructured photocatalyst designed to promote direct Z-scheme charge transfer for visible-light hydrogen evolution. The key idea is that interfacial Mo–S bonding plus an internally generated electric field, together with sulfur vacancies in ZnIn2S4, suppress recombination and boost charge separation, yielding a high H2 evolution rate of 63.21 mmol g−1 h−1 and AQY of 76.48% at 420 nm.",
